<body>
  <h1>Task 1: HTML, CSS, and JS Fundamentals</h1>
  <section>
    <h2>1. Understand HTML Structure</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Learn basic structure of web pages using HTML.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Practice using tags like headings, paragraphs, links, images, lists, tables, and forms.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Learn CSS Styling</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Style HTML elements with CSS.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Use selectors, properties, and values to change colors, layout, spacing, and fonts. Try Flexbox and Grid.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Explore JavaScript Basics</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Make web pages interactive.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Use variables, functions, events, loops, and conditionals. Try simple DOM manipulation like changing text, toggling classes, and responding to button clicks.
    </div>
  </section>

  <h1>Task 2: Mini Projects</h1>
  <section>
    <h2>1. Create a Calculator</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to perform calculations.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Build a basic calculator interface. Implement functions for add, subtract, multiply, and divide.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Build an Image Gallery</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Work with layouts and event handling.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Display multiple images. Add click events to enlarge or change views.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Make a Quiz App</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Practice form handling and conditionals.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Display questions, accept answers, and show scores.
    </div>
  </section>

  <h1>Task 3: Advanced Concepts</h1>
  <section>
    <h2>1. Responsive Web Design</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Adapt layout to various devices.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Use media queries and flexible grids to ensure responsiveness on phones, tablets, and desktops.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. JavaScript Timers and Events</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Handle time-based functions.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Create a countdown timer or digital clock using <code>setInterval</code> and <code>setTimeout</code>.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Animation with CSS/JS</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Bring life to elements.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Animate elements using CSS transitions or JavaScript. Create hover effects or sliding menus.
    </div>
  </section>

  <h1>Task 4: Full Project Implementation</h1>
  <section>
    <h2>1. Build a Personal Portfolio</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Showcase skills and projects.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Design and develop a personal portfolio site including sections for bio, projects, contact form, etc.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Create a To-Do List Application</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Implement interactivity with JavaScript.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Build a to-do list where users can add, delete, and mark tasks. Use local storage for saving tasks.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Develop a Product Listing Page</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Practice layout and data handling.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Build a product listing with filters and sorting features. Show image, name, price, and sort them by name/price.
    </div>
  </section>

  <h1>Task 5: Final Project and Optimization</h1>
  <p><strong>Timeline:</strong> 9 Days</p>

  <section>
    <h2>1. Build a Full Web Application (Capstone Project)</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Integrate all skills into one complete web app.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Develop a final project (e.g., an e-commerce site, blog, or advanced portfolio) with dynamic features, using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Optimize for Performance</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Ensure the application runs efficiently and loads quickly.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Minimize CSS and JavaScript files, apply lazy loading for images, reduce the number of HTTP requests, and optimize load times.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Ensure Cross-Browser Compatibility and Mobile Responsiveness</h2>
    <div class="project-box">
      <strong>Objective:</strong> Guarantee the application works on all major browsers and devices.<br>
      <strong>Actions:</strong> Test the project on Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and mobile browsers, fixing any compatibility or display issues.
    </div>
  </section>
